Name: Aaron Carback
Biography: My name is Aaron Carback, I am a photographer from Baltimore Maryland. After returning from a pediatric physical therapy internship in South Africa, my passion for those in need has exploded. My faith in Jesus Christ fuels an internal drive to love the poor, weak, and fatherless. Through photography, and the appropriate platform to bring attention, education, and further humanitarian effort, I believe that I can change the world. I am looking for an aggressive NGO desperate to go to the ends of the world in order to serve those in need and tell "Other"s how they can help.

Name: Albert GonzÃ¡lez Farran
Biography: My name is Albert Gonzalez Farran (Barcelona, 1975). I'm an independent photojournalist and videographer with 18 years experience. I'm currently based in Juba, South Sudan, taking photo and video assignments for Agence France Presse and humanitarian organizations. I was the photographer of the UN peacekeeping mission in Darfur and later I conducted multimedia and film documentaries about migrations for several organizations. Earlier, I worked for media outlets in Spain, Peru and Ireland and conducted personal photo projects in Bosnia and Ethiopia. Degree in Catalan Studies, he has a Master of Arts in Photojournalism and Documentary Photography from the University of the Arts of London (2013) and a postgraduate in Communication for Development from the Universitat Pompeu Fabra in Barcelona (2005).

Name: CMRD Ali Bukar
Biography: My name is ALI BUKAR,a photographer,activist,peace promoter and advocate for good governance. Am interested in political and humanatarian photography. Am into photography because of what's going on in my states,how people define the state to "Other"s.with my knowledge of photography,we shoot, share with the world how my state is living in peace but not how people define it.

Name: Altamash Askari
Biography: I am Altamash, I am a hobbyist armature photographer. I have special interests in landscape photography, street & documentary and astrophotography. In past I have done a lot of portfolio photo shoots, done a few weddings and engagements as well.

Name: Andrew Kartende
Biography: I am a freelance documentary photographer and visual story teller. Often describing my work as being situated in the intersection of fine art and photojournalism. My passion lies in helping organizations raise awareness and tell stories through photography, and my experience comes from working with people from different industries and backgrounds and understanding meta-narratives. I am driven by the combination of utmost curiosity and the adventure of just getting into locations to get the right shots.

Name: Artur Francisco
Biography: I am Artur and I live in beautiful TÄmaki Makaurau / Auckland. I was born in Brazil and grew up photographing, drawing, painting and doing everything with a flavour visual arts I could get my hands on. I photograph because I love it â€“ it is that simple. I am a visual storyteller and specialise in NGO, development and wedding photography. When I am not photographing people who are making the world a better place or beautiful brides and grooms on their special day, I can be found strolling around Auckland, phone in hand, looking for â€˜theâ€™ perfect composition or just shooting silly things that look pretty.

Name: Aung Naing Soe
Biography: I started working as a fixer since last five years ago. Then, I inspired in working as a photographer. I started to cover for local media and I kept working as a fixer. Since last over two years ago, some of my works were published in International Media such as TIME, The Guardian, Asia Nikkei, Global Post, Daily mail, Al Jazeera etc. And also, I had some assignments from International Organizations such as Africa Interactive and some UN Agencies and some NGOs.

Name: Aydin Matlabi
Biography: My name is Aydin Matlabi, I am a humanitarian artist and my works challenge the vision of how we perceive our global world. Having been raised in the urban environment of Montreal, I had the privilege to grow up in a community who stood for human rights, woman rights and equality. However, as I started to work in developing countries and war zones I become more aware of the many cultural obstaclesâ€™ that prevent us from relating to the many social problems in those nations. As an artist my main purpose is to create art that help the suppressed communities and create a voice for them. Having worked in Haiti, Afganistan, South Tailand, Iraq, Iran, DRC and many more countries who struggle for liberty, I will risk it all to create narratives and stories in order to provide visibility for human right. My art finds strength and humanity in the most difficult places. I have built a none for profit (www.foundation64.org) that creates sustainable visuals for grass roots organization who support woman right and child protection. Therefore, better representing the powerful work they do. With all financial gained is directly deposited in the organizations account. In addition, with support and training, I will teach the locals to document them self. Creating powerful visuals is not enough, we need to find sustainable solutions. Supporting, education and giving the power to does who have lost it.

Name: Beth LaBerge
Biography: A lifelong photography lover, over the past 10 years I have gained a wide range of experience. Whether itâ€™s the fast-paced world of photojournalism working for the San Francisco Examiner, archival and marketing shoots for San Francisco Museum of Modern Art, events for Orange Photography or documentary work for non-profits, I feel at ease with any circumstance. My BA in Cultural Anthropology from San Francisco State gives me a cultural understanding of the world and my studies at the City College of San Francisco for photojournalism helped me hone my camera and writing skills.

Name: Brian Frank
Biography: Brian C. Frank is an award-winning freelance photojournalist from Des Moines, Iowa. Photographing for The New York Times, Reuters and Polaris Images, Brianâ€™s images have been seen in publications and on websites around the world. Selections from Fight Night have been shown on the New York Times Lens blog, Burn Magazine, and in gallery exhibits in Des Moines, Minneapolis and New York. Brian began studying photography on a part-time basis as a creative outlet. Those classes quickly developed into a passion, but he did not know what he wanted to do. It was not until the first anniversary of hurricane Katrina that he found the direction. Always being a bit of an activist, Brian was angered that a year after the hurricane hit, a great city like New Orleans was still in ruins. After spending a week in New Orleans photographing the devastation and talking to the residents, he found that telling stories with the camera was what he needed to do.

Name: Chris Bavaria
Biography: I have been taking pictures since I was 13 and my father put me in charge of the camera on our family vacation. I then immersed myself in my local punk scene, taking photos of bandsâ€” something that has taken me around the world many times over and has lead to my work being published anywhere from Playboy to AOL. At the same time, I received a BA in Art/ Photography from Millersville University and an MFA in documentary photography from the Academy of Art University in San Francisco. Following grad school I moved back to the East Coast and continued working in photojournalism and portraiture for folks like The Travel Channel, Brooklyn Vegan, and NPR. For the past 8 years in Virginia I've been teaching photography at Thomas Nelson Community College & Christopher Newport University.

Name: David Verberckt
Biography:
I am an independent reportage photographer currently living in Budapest, Hungary.
Iâ€™ve graduated photography in Brussels in 1993, and afterwards the International Development. After exhibiting my first documentary reportages in the early nineties, Iâ€™ve turned to the aid agencies and have spent twenty years working in humanitarian emergency and development with several international organisations worldwide.
In early 2013, I left the ordinary offices to devote my professional career again fully to photography. I am keeping my photographic work close to people, their destinies, hence my reportages portray peculiarities of an often deprived civil society affected by latent or bygone conflict.
I have since been working on several projects such as Frozen Conflicts in the Caucasus depicting the ordinary people whose life is in limbo following the conflicts of the nineties and Palestinian Chronicles as a continuation of the series taken in early nineties, focusing on the daily realities of the numerous refugee camps' population. Recently, I am working on subjects depicting hard labour and seasonal migration flows in the overpopulated Bengal bay and documenting statelessness of Bihari and Rohingya.Â

Name: Dominik Tschhitsch
Biography: Dominik Tschitsch | Cameraman | Photographer | | Freelancer | I like yellow things : bananas , taxis and snow ðŸ“ Munich

Name: Dominique Felicity Chapman
Biography: My name is Dominique, I'm a professional travel photographer whose got 6+ years experience and a passion for creating a difference. I have gone onto study a Certificate in Travel Writing and Photography, Certificate in Dino 101: Dinosaur Paleobiology (with the University of Alberta) and am currently studying a double bachelor in Art and Science majoring in Anthropology and Environment & sustainability at University of South Queensland. I'm willing to travel anywhere and have an interest in conservation and human rights photography. My photography and videography has been used in magazine and ad campaigns throughout the world but I would love to move into more personal photography.

Name: Dora Damian
Biography: Iâ€™ve always had a flair for storytelling which manifests itself across various genres, from fine art to adventure sports. Whether it's capturing athletes who constantly push their limits, or a landscape changed through human interaction, it became apparent that thereâ€™s a common denominator in my work: the human presence - and its traces. I document life, with a current focus on humanitarian projects.

Name: Ehsan Hazaveh
Biography: Ehsan Hazaveh is an Iranian independent photographer based in Wellington, New Zealand. He has been focusing on social, environmental, and political issues. He started working as a newspaper photographer in 2011 at the Iranian Labour News Agency. In 2012, he began working on personal projects, on subjects such as people living in remote environments and displaced people. He has been awarded the â€œYoung Talent of Social Documentary Photographyâ€ two times from the Sheed Award in 2012 and 2013. Ehsan studied Master of Graphic Design at the University of Tehran. He is doing a PhD in Media Studies at Victoria University of Wellington.

Name: Emma Coombe
Biography: Emma Coombe is a freelance visual storyteller experienced in documentary and commercial work. She is passionate about the use of photography as a tool for awareness and change, whether this be through documentary projects or staged narratives. With a background in both photography and international development, she has the necessary tools to convey accurate and impactful stories. Emma is available for any assignments and collaborations, and is currently based in Auckland, New Zealand.

Name: Eric G Hernandez
Biography: Brooklyn based photographer, who loves to travel the world in order to capture raw images that will provide a new platform for new subjects of all walks of life. I am interested in working with NGO's that deal with Humanitarian Issues as well as disaster relief and refugee support.

Name: Felicia Simion
Biography: I am a 23-year-old photographer and retoucher based in Bucharest, Romania. I graduated from the Bucharest National University of Arts (Photography and Video department) in 2016 and I am currently pursuing a Masterâ€™s Degree in Ethnology, Cultural Anthropology and Folklore at the University of Bucharest. I discovered photography at the age of 13, when I fell in love with the works of Magnum photographers, while being inspired at the same time by young emerging artists. My photographic universe is filled both with fantasy and realism â€“ I have an eye to witness the seen and one to perceive the unseen. My work is the result of my love for people and nature and the peculiarities of daily life. Available for commissions around the world.

Name: Fred Moseley
Biography: My name is Fred Moseley, I have worked as a volunteer photographer for the last seven years in a Cultural house. Schlesische27. Before that I owned and operated a commercial studio, in Saint Louis, Missouri. I have many years experience as a photographer. I would like to travel and have my expenses paid as well as some income as well.

Name: Gil Gilmour
Biography: My name is Gil and I am a photographer from Melbourne, Australia. I've been working in the photographic industry for the past decade and after using photography to describe just about everything one could, the only images that affect me are ones created in truth, for good. Now that I have left all "Other" photographic commitments to be the master navigator of my own seas, I want to use my eyes for the betterment of this human experience we share.

Name: Hannah Shiver
Biography: I'm an aspiring photographer. I just took my first paI'd job for a major corporation to shoot content for their social media. I really enjoy capturing the beauty of everyday things that people overlook.

Name: Jared Buckley
Biography: My name is Jared Buckley and I am a 27 year old New Zealander who has a passion for using both my photography and videography skills to bring about positive change. I am currently based in New Zealand but am heading to both South East Asia and Europe in the second half of 2019. I am a visual storyteller and am interested in working with any NGOs that need there stories told.

Name: Jessica Amity
Biography: My name is Jessica Amity and I specialise in portraiture and documentary photography. Although I'm half British and half Italian I was raised in Nepal, where I've spent the majority of my life. The goal with my photography is to show the beauty, resilience and strength of the people I photograph as well as discover and share stories that I believe should be heard. I am currently based in Kathmandu, Nepal but travel abroad often for work. I am looking for work opportunities around the world but also close to home that will challenge me as well as benefit the organisations objectives to make a difference. I am currently freelancing but I am looking for organisations that work within the humanitarian sector. (However, I would gladly take on any project) :)

Name: Johanna Merenheimo
Biography: I am a professional photographer, originally from Finland but now based in New Zealand. Back in Finland I worked many years in studios focusing on commercial work and portraits & events which areas I specialized while studying and achieving my further qualification in photography. Now, that I've recently moved to New Zealand, I'm fascinated about this culture and nature around me and I'm aiming to learn more of it through my camera. I capture events and I capture portraits but I do have a passion to capture products as well. In New Zealand or anywhere in the world.

Name: Josephine Ki
Biography:
Freelance Australian documentary photographer with over 10 years of professional experience as well as experience with NGO photography (All Hands Volunteers, HELP Nepal) currently based in Asia.Â 

Digital nomad seeking long / short term contract anywhere in the world as well as remote work opportunities.

Name: Julia Schoenstaedt
Biography: Hailing from Berlin, Julia SchÃ¶nstÃ¤dt is an award winning freelance photographer and video maker, who earned her Masters at Goldsmiths (University of London) and has gone on to have journalistic works published with The Guardian, der Spiegel, Huffington Post and many more. Over the past three years she has covered the compelling criminal case of Ms. Stacey Hyde, who was acquitted and released in May 2015 with the help of Justice for Woman, a campaigning organisation whom SchÃ¶nstÃ¤dt partnered with on the case. In 2012, SchÃ¶nstÃ¤dt and her partners founded â€œThe 16 Bars Projectâ€, a multi-media collaborative project working with the aim to raise awareness of the penal system through the medium of art. In 2014, her persistence to gain access to the German prison system and subsequent body of work was recognized with an award from The Guardian. At the centre of her work stands always the â€˜human elementâ€™. SchÃ¶nstÃ¤dt seeks out stories on people who have faced challenges and indeed are challenged by life itself. Through her photographic and video works, the thread of an anthropological line is deeply woven. ---- Besides my London based commercial photography I am passionate for travel and social projects. I love to meet people and learn about their life and their culture.

Name: Karen Abplanalp
Biography:
My name is Karen Abplanalp, born in Switzerland and raised in New Zealand. I am a multi-award winning photojournalist who travelled to West Papua in 2016 - the first TV crew to visit the Indonesian ruled Melanesian region in 50 years. Trained as a fashion photographer, I followed my passion for people and social justice, leading to the publication of stories from; Timor Leste, Solomon Islands, Indonesia, Belgium, UK, New Zealand, India, Fiji, West Papua and Samoa. Stories include;
Following a womenâ€™s theatre group, Stages of Change, who use theatre to reduce violence against women and children in the Solomon Islands. A multi-award winning investigation into the world's largest gold mine in West Papua amid allegations of human rights violations and severe environmental damage. I have worked on projects for the British Council, European Union, UNICEF along with many small, grassroots organisations. I love to collaborate so please get in touch with your ideas and see what we can achieve together.

Name: Kitty Norwell
Biography: A developing documentary photographer currently working within third sector communications. I am currently building a not for profit documentary style portfolio to enable me to complete an MA in photojournalism at London College of Communication. I completed my BA in photography at the Arts University in Bournemouth in 2013. During my studies I worked as a freelance events photographer. Since graduating I have progressed to work for The Big Issue as a photography teacher, Age UK as a communications officer and at Oxfam as an archivist intern. I am no longer freelance full time, but work commissions and in kind photographic work around my full time work.

Name: Ksu Postolnik
Biography: Hi, Iâ€™m Ksu. Raised in the Caucasus Mountains region of Russia, I left home at 17 to study natural sciences in Moscow State University. After the graduation, I worked for Garmin as a cartographer, and it is there that I became interested in travelling and photography. I later moved to California, where I now run my photography business, and also teach Natural Sciences at a Russian Heritage school. I live in San Jose with my boyfriend, Genaro, who makes the most delicious tacos in the world, and who makes me really happy every day. Photographing nature and people constantly reminds me that the Universe is on our side, the world is alive and breathing, and nature is worth fighting for. I love people and I love meeting cultures and I love immersing myself into their ways of life. And if I can capture these situations on a camera and show the rest of the world, itâ€™s opening their eyes. We live in such a fairytale kind of environment. For us to see what such a huge percentage of the world is living in or coping with â€“ I think we need to see it. And hopefully it triggers that want in us to help.

Name: Laura Horton
Biography: My name is Laura, and Iâ€™m very interested in using images to give voices to those who have none. Iâ€™m passionate about animal welfare.

Name: Liam Leslie
Biography: I am a photographer based in London whose work mainly focuses on social issues. My most recent body of work focuses on London's luxury shopping area Bond Street and the sharp wealth inequality of the area. With high end designer stores contrasted with a growing servant class of cleaners and a further subclass of homeless individuals who sleep in the doorways.

Name: Lola Wallace
Biography: Born and raised in Londonâ€™s east end, I went to school with kids whose parents came from all over the world, it was an incredible mix of cultures. My own parents had settled in London when they were children, dad from Trinidad in the West Indies, my mum from Guyana in South America, so I thrived in such a diverse environment. After school, I went to university gaining a BA Hons degrees in Cultural Studies, which in turn led to my fascination with peopleâ€™s unique stories, where they came from, how it had shaped them and where they may be headed. About that same time, Iâ€™d started to develop a keen interest in photography, so it seemed obvious that this would work as a fine medium to try to capture, in a singular moment, some aspect, some fragment of these peoples lives.

Name: Matthieu Lunard
Biography: I have extensive experience in image research, which is intimately related to my career as a professional photographer working in the industry since 2003. In Paris, I worked with a notable list of diverse clients including Elite, Ford, Viva, Women, and Karin & Silent model agencies. During my time living in China I worked for prestigious publications such as Vogue China, Lâ€™Officiel, Madame Figaro, Milk Magazine, Ilook magazine, Modern Weekly and many more. I also cooperated on various advertisement campaigns for Hilton Hotels, Martell Cognac, and Elite World and China model competitions. As a result, I have extensive knowledge and confidence in navigating the ins-and-outs of the photographic medium and industry. My expertise in the photography industry extends beyond my work as a professional photographer. In 2012, following my relocation to Bangkok, I co-founded an online photography and lifestyle magazine called www.aserica.com. This project has allowed me to expand my skills in coordinating photo-shoots, conducting image research, developing visual identities, as well as approaching ideas using diverse and innovative editorial angles both in lifestyle and fashion. In addition, I co-founded and curated an online contemporary gallery named Weissprint (www.weissprint.com), providing me with new skills in managing photographers and selling their work. It should also be noted that I have lived in the Asia-Pacific region for more than 15 years in culturally vibrant cities including Hanoi, Shanghai, Beijing, Sydney, and Bangkok. These precious years have provided me with very intimate insights into the region and its people, allowing me to develop nuanced communication skills and a taste for exploration.

Name: Megan Dutriou
Biography: I'm a novice photographer, but I'm driven by boundless curiosity to capture stories that are both artful and significant. Best described as documentary photography, my style favours the candid public scene, while both urban and natural settings form the backdrop to the personal, human narratives at the core of my work. Compositional experimentation and a knack for timing (or just plain luck) are my most indispensable photographic tools, and my favourite images are unstaged and spontaneous - ones that record moments of coincidental clarity or meaningful chance amidst the chaos of everyday human activity.

Name: Muhammad Bukar Umara
Biography: Muhammad Bukar Umara is a documentary photographer and a digital storyteller, based in Nigeria. His storytelling work are social-impact driven with much focus on "Out-of-School" children in Nigeria and The Boko Haram humanitarian crisis in the northeast. In his regular job, he works in the humanitarian and development sector. He also founded the Co-Development Hub, a capacity building hub for leadership development and skill development.

Name: Muhammad Iqbal Muhd Yamin
Biography: Hi, My name is Muhammad Iqbal Mohd Yamin. I am a Street Photographer/ Photojournalist. Im looking for opportunities to work anywhere. Im also good with graphic design.

Name: Muhammad Rafique
Biography:
I am Muhammad rafique. I m Rohingya refugee living in Bangladesh refugee camp.My dream is to become a photographer.I am apart of WFP
Storytellers.

Name: Musa Ishiaku e
Biography: My name is Musa, I am a documentary photographer from North East Nigeria looking for work opportunities around world. I am currently working with USAID and would be interested in working with NGO's that deal with humanitarian activities.

Name: Nando Azevedo
Biography:
I was fortunate enough to be born and raised in Rio de Janeiro, a city that shows no mercy and holds no illusions (except during carnival when itâ€™s all about masquerading reality). Growing up there allowed me to witness the worst and the best of our species.

I have travelled extensively to understand the illusions that entrap, limit and at the same time define us as early 21st century humans, and hopefully my work  portraits a little bit of that. I have to admit I am a little bit embarrassed about being human but I am also hopeful: I am one of those romantic people who still believes in mankind. I believe that we can redeem ourselves, and start living with respect and dignity regardless of race, nationality or any "Other" imposed separation.

My mission is to help us achieve emancipation by changing the way people see the world and their relationship with "Other"s. Photography just happened to be they way I chose to achieve that.  Although I pay my bills with commercial photography & videography work, my true passion is in social documentary and at the moment I am working on transitioning to being a full time social documentarist.

I am also very grateful to be alive in such decisive times and I love meeting and working with people and organizations that are also working towards the same goals. So if what I said resonates with your own mission please do get in touch.

Name: Ouadah Mustapha
Biography: My name is Mustapha, I'm studying protection and restoration of cultural inheritage. I'm from Algiers, Algeria . I consider myself as a street photographer . It's always fascinating for me, to walk the streets with my camera trying to find order and balance in a seeming chaos . Cities are my playground, where humans are the center of my work. The most challenging part is trying to find greatness in ordinary thing and daily life. Beauty and harmony are everywhere, and it's up to the photographer to snap the photograph at the right moment . Day after day, my vision is evolving on my society, photography brought me a more human contact with people and strangers that I wouldn't have known without photography. There's in every street's corner a story to be told and an encouter to be done .

Name: Roun Ry
Biography:
My names's Roun Ry. Since 2010 I have attended the annual Anjali workshops in Siem Reap, Cambodia, and personally trained by Paolo Patrizi, World Press Photo award winner.

I'm currently working on a project, shooting the impact of deforestation in Cambodia.

I love photographing people and landscape. I love shooting in color but I prefer Black and White photographs.Â 

I can speak and write both Khmer and English well and I am well connected with the local NGO community.

Name: Ryan James
Biography: I live in New Zealand with my wife and 3 children, the youngest is just 1 year old and was born 16 weeks premature at 24 weeks of gestation here in New Zealand, she has a few medical conditions but is doing well, my middle child was born in Brazil 3 years ago and our oldest is 9 and was born in Australia. For a while I was making my living making promotional videos and I swore I wouldn't get into photography, the idea of every image being studied for mistakes made me feel like it was too much, but I shot some things for family and before you know it I was working for major international brands - from there the rest is history. For commercial work I have a business named Braziwi Media and for weddings and family work I operate as Ryan James Photography.

Name: Schoo Flemming
Biography:
Schoo Flemming Photography Film




South Africa based German photographer Schoo Flemming has studied photography and filmmaking and has been working as a freelance video editing supervisor and photographer for more than 15 years.




He took part in a wide range of professional German tv productions such as tv advertising, documentaries, history features, business-to-business communication, political campaigns (Germany nationwide) and was member of the team that was awarded with Corporate Media "Member of the European Masterclass".
He also was significantly involved in several productions for childrens` television being awarded with GermanyÂ´s most prestigious tv-award, the "Grimme Preis".




Apart of his commercial achievements Schoo Flemming has ever since traveled the world with his photo camera.




Schoo Flemming currently lives in Cape Town, South Africa.




Education:
FH Dortmund, University of Applied Sciences and Arts.
Diploma 1999.

Name: Serena Stevenson
Biography: Internationally awarded documentary photographer and film maker Serena Stevenson mostly focuses on culture, community and human connection. Serena works both commercially and with NGO's. Serena has a wide knowledge and practice in multi platform story telling and also has a participatory story facilitation company which hands the power to the subject to make, edit and share their own stories. www.speakstory.co 'Being half Italian and raised in Auckland has instilled in me a great faith in humanity. I love the spontaneity of the diverse world we live in, where belonging is everywhere. I have a strong belief that story is in everything, and we can make a difference with our creativity. I often say it's the David Attenborough approach, share the magic of humanity in hope it will inspire us to preserve nature and all life. My Nonna (Grandm"Other") came from Calabria, Italy to Melbourne after the War WW2 for a better life. She lived, loved and worked in a foreign land with her husband and ten children to build a future. From this I learned the value of simplicity and it is my aim to always find the simple solutions in work and life. No matter how the channels change, emotive storytelling will always be at the core of my purpose.' Serena Stevenson

Name: Shayne Robinson
Biography: Multi-faceted Shayne Robinson is a son of the diverse culture of the Rainbow Nation, a photographer, videographer and a journalist who is inspired by the elaborate forms of life that surround him on a daily basis. His collection of work greatly reflects the passion he feels for Africa and the betterment thereof. Over more than 15 years, Shayne has worked in over 34 countries around the world covering everything from civil wars and natural disasters to corporate and sporting events.Shayne has always had a close link to the subjects that he photographs often finding himself conflicted and wanting to do more to help them. In 2005 a project about a ballet school in Alexandra township that he spent a year working on, earned him a 1st prize, Arts, and Entertainment in the prestigious World Press Photo competition. As a result of this recognition, he was able to raise a substantial amount of funds to help support the school. Shayneâ€™s work has been published in all of the local and most international newspapers and magazines, including The Star, Mail & Guardian, The New York Times, The Globe and Mail, Sunday Times (UK), National Geographic and Russian Vogue. Shayne has also been the recipient of the Fujifilm Press Photographer of the year award, CNN African Journalist award and the Mondi Awards. Some of Shayneâ€™s clients include Greenpeace, Section 27, IFAW, The Treatment Action Campaign and Save South Africa. Shayne loves nothing more than immersing himself in the stories that he is working on and brings this passion to every single job he works on, no matter how big or small it may be.

Name: Stephane Lanoux
Biography: Stephane Lanoux is a French photographer based in Paris. For the past years, he has been focusing on intimate life and the persistence of people living in remote environments specifically in Middle East, South Africa and Asia. He has exhibited at the Dubai Photography Festival 2014, Paris galleries and has been regularly featured in various photography magazines.

Name: Stephen Huff
Biography: While attending university in Illinois, I began to pursue a degree in Photojournalism. In my third year, I had to ask my parents for financial help. My father agreed to help only if I majored in business. I have my BS degree in Statistical Economics. I spent the last 23 years in the corporate area of medical device technology performing mergers & acquisitions for some of the largest players in that space. I have lived in 6 different countries in North America, Europe, and Asia and have gained a broad, global appreciation for the state of healthcare, and also humanity across the globe. Last year, I came across a website called, "When To Jump". It encourages one to follow their passion. I did. I jumped out of the corporate world and I am pursuing my dream of photojournalism with a focus on humanitarian issues and causes. All of my work thus far, as I build my business portfolio, has been pro-bono. I have just started to charge for services feeling pretty good about the quality of the portfolio I've built.

Name: takeshi shinohara
Biography: My name is Takeshi Shinohara, a freelance photographer based in the Philippines and Japan. I often do commercial photography and work for Philippines based NGO.

Name: Teanna Woods Okojie
Biography:
Hello, I'm Tee {Teanna} Professional Photographer, Visual Storyteller & Producer. Creating & curating thought provoking, emotionally stimulating visual content for your NGO, Social Enterprise, Global Missions, B Corporations, Cultural Narratives & "Other" humanitarian organizations. As we collaborate together to reach your global community,your principle vision is kept at the forefront. We'll ethically & positively highlight your organizations global vision, while engaging and educating individuals to the cause at hand. Together we'll create purpose driven content.
Based in New York and Lagos

Name: Todd Henry
Biography: My name is Todd Henry. I was born in the United States but I have lived in New Zealand for over a decade. I enjoy taking documentary style photos that serve as accurate representations of a people or a place. My academic background in anthropology informs my approach to photography and gives me a unique perspective on the world. I love travelling and I have a special affinity for the people and cultures that are found in the South Pacific regions of Polynesia and Melanesia.

Name: Tolu Oluwapojuwo
Biography: My name is Tolu Oluwapojuwo. I am a documentary photographer with keen interest in telling untold day to day stories. I have been involved in personal projects like Nigeria Everyday, Stories of Nigeria and many more and looking for work opportunities around the world.

Name: Usman Maigana
Biography: My name is Usman Muhammad Maigana,a photographer and advocate for peace based in Maiduguri.I do photography to portray my State on a positive light and make people outside know that yes even with the insurgency we still pick up from the ruins and move on with our day to day activities.

Name: Vanessa Endeley
Biography: I am a 23 year old Nigerian Photographer and for the longest time Photography has been the medium through which I am able to express myself. Being an introvert plus an only child I grew up speaking very little words, but with my Camera and Photos I have gotten the push to interact with those around me more than I was used to. My preferred style of Photography is documentary Photography simply because of it's authenticity, no plans or alterations are made and what you see is basically what you get. I love to travel to places I wouldnâ€™t normally go, interact with the locals, learn new things about them and explore new places which is a good way to expand my knowledge and exposure. I make it a point to note the importance of understanding your subject because I believe if there is no communication and understanding between the Camera, the subject and the Photographer then the Photo as a finished product of your interaction will not communicate the accurate emotions to itâ€™s viewer (s). This is interpreted in my Photographs as I hope youâ€™ll see in my work. Being able to see, experience and document the various realities of different human beings spread out across villages, towns, cities, countries and continents is what motivates me to keep pushing and doing what I know how to do best, Photography.

Name: Victoria Lodi
Biography: My name is Victoria. I am a documentary photographer based in New York City. I use my photography skills to help people. I want to create content that can be used for social change. Extensive travel in Asia, the Middle East, South and Central America have shaped my my worldview. Though my travels, I have learned that people are more similar than different. I am interested in working with NGOs that are in the trenches doing the hard work to make a difference in people's lives.

Name: Yunesh Bajracharya
Biography: I am yunesh, and used to work in INGO as a communication officer, through there got an opportunities make photo stories and documentary. I love doing portrait and photo story photography. I am interested to work to for an INGOs for a official works too.

Name: Zachary Allard
Biography: My name is Zachary Allard and I am a documentary style photographer located in Phoenix, AZ. I'm interested in work opportunities anywhere in the world. I have worked in commercial photography in the past as well as for local newspapers. As of recently I've worked with Feed Hope International in Malawi, and absolutely loved it. I'm interested in working with all types of NGOs covering any sort of humanitarian issue.
